    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hope this is the right way to do this.\r\n\r\nSee https://github.com/ap/vim-buftabline/issues/8#issuecomment-124977497.\r\n\r\nGiven that buffers are really what we'd call tabs in other programs (e.g. browsers or terminals), it'd be ideal if it was possible to treat them the same way.\r\n\r\n- [vim-buftabline](https://github.com/ap/vim-buftabline) allows you to see a \"buffer bar\".\r\n- `:bn`, `:bp`, and `:b 5` allow you to easily switch between them\r\n\r\nBut there isn't a good way (as far as I know) to change the order of the buffers in the buffer list, maybe a move buffer and a swap buffer command.\r\n\r\nI know some plugins get around this by implementing their own virtual buffer list, but that seems bug-prone.\r\n\r\nDoes this seem reasonable? Sorry if it's a duplicate, had a look but didn't find anything.",
