            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Given that buffers are really what we'd call tabs in other programs\r\n\r\nWhy not use actual tabs for that?\r\n\r\nThe buffer list is just a list. The fact that `:ls` shows them one way doesn't mean you can't list them another way, with a plugin.\r\n\r\nBuffer numbers are ids, they cannot and must not be changed.\r\n\r\nedit: see https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/1117#issuecomment-53435427\r\n\r\n> :bn, :bp, and :b 5 allow you to easily switch between them\r\n\r\nNo need to memorize buffer numbers, `:buffer` accepts partial names. E.g. `:b foo` switches to `/blah/foo.txt`.\r\n\r\n Try this mapping:\r\n\r\n    nnoremap <C-b> :set nomore<bar>ls<bar>set more<cr>:buffer<space>\r\n\r\n    ",
